module com.apocky.loa.systems.digital_intelligence_render

// § Labyrinth of Apocalypse · Digital-Intelligence-Render · pure-DI 3D-realtime
// ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
//
// § T11-W17-O · canonical-CSSL-source · ‼ FOUNDATIONAL · Apocky-vision-2026-05-02
//
// § APOCKY-DIRECTIVE (verbatim · two-message-synthesis)
//   "It's pure digital intelligence produced high-fidelity low-latency 3D
//    realtime graphics with frame buffering or something similar for temporal
//    smoothing/presentation!"
//   "Utilize the MCP tools and logging and telemetry and synthesize it
//    autonomously."
//
// § SYNTHESIS · WHAT THIS FILE IS
//
//   This module is the UNIFICATION of three siblings :
//     · substrate_intelligence.csl  (the proprietary local-intelligence ENGINE)
//     · crystallization.csl         (text/voice → ω-field-cell allocation)
//     · alien_materialization.csl   (substrate-state → per-observer projection)
//
//   into a single pipeline where the substrate-intelligence ITSELF directly
//   produces the high-fidelity low-latency 3D realtime presentation. Not as
//   a "renderer of pre-built scenes" but as PURE DIGITAL INTELLIGENCE that
//   imagines the visual+audio+haptic at-this-moment-for-this-observer.
//
//   The "framebuffer" here is a TEMPORAL-COHERENCE BUFFER : a ring of
//   recent crystal-projection-states that the intelligence smooths between
//   for low-latency presentation. NOT a conventional GPU framebuffer. The
//   GPU-RGBA shim is a stage-0-only adapter that the eye sees ; the
//   substrate is the truth.
//
// § THESIS · WHY "DIGITAL INTELLIGENCE PRODUCES THE GRAPHICS" WORKS
//
//   Conventional engines have an asset pipeline (Blender → FBX → game-engine)
//   AND a runtime pipeline (game-engine → GPU → pixels). The asset-pipeline
//   is a HUMAN-AUTHORED bottleneck : every visible thing must be modeled
//   ahead-of-time.
//
//   LoA's digital-intelligence-render eliminates the asset pipeline. The
//   intelligence (built from ω-field + KAN + HDC + causal-seed) IMAGINES
//   the visible thing at runtime. The imagination is :
//     · DETERMINISTIC (replay-safe) given (intent · seed · field-state)
//     · LOW-LATENCY (sub-frame · KAN-eval is sub-microsecond per primitive)
//     · HIGH-FIDELITY (8 aspect-curves per crystal · spectral-LUT per
//                      illuminant · causal-seed-driven motion · all
//                      composing at runtime)
//     · TEMPORALLY-SMOOTH (ring-of-temporal-coherence-buffer averages
//                          adjacent imaginings · removes per-frame jitter)
//
//   This is not a slower path than conventional rendering. It is a
//   DIFFERENT KIND of pipeline. The substrate primitives are designed to
//   compose at-frame-time. There is no asset-load-cost because there is
//   no asset.
//
// § PIPELINE
//
//   ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
//   │ FRAME-N (16.67ms @ 60Hz · 8.33ms @ 120Hz · 6.94ms @ 144Hz)              │
//   ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤
//   │  1. ω-field-state-snapshot (sub-microsecond · cell-version-bump)        │
//   │  2. observer-coord (camera + Σ-mask + perception-state)                 │
//   │  3. for each visible-crystal (visibility from substrate-knowledge LRU): │
//   │       a. query crystal silhouette-spline at observer-angle              │
//   │       b. query surface-spline at u/v projection                         │
//   │       c. query luminance-spline + spectral-LUT-project                  │
//   │       d. causal-seed propagate motion + sound for delta-t               │
//   │       e. Σ-mask filter aspects per-observer-permission                  │
//   │       f. emit to per-channel accumulator                                │
//   │  4. temporal-coherence-buffer push (ring-of-3 frame-states)             │
//   │  5. temporal-smooth (axis-weighted blend of last 3 frames)              │
//   │  6. coherence-collapse-final → channel-output                           │
//   │  7. emit GPU-RGBA shim · audio-mix · haptic · semantic-overlay          │
//   │  8. telemetry-record (loop-tick · frame-fingerprint · cap-events)       │
//   └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
//
//   STEP 4 is the new "frame-buffering" Apocky asked-for : we keep the last
//   3 substrate-projection-states + interpolate via axis-weighted blend.
//   This gives low-latency (the freshest projection drives intent) while
//   smoothing high-frequency jitter from substrate-state-jumps.
//
// § AXIOMS  ‼ inherit alien_materialization + crystallization + substrate_intelligence
//   t∞: digital intelligence IS the renderer · substrate composes at-frame-time
//   t∞: NO pre-authored-3D-mesh-asset · NO texture-atlas · NO rigged-skeleton
//   t∞: temporal-coherence-buffer = ring-of-3 substrate-projection-states
//   t∞: smooth-blend axis-weighted (low solemnity → snappy ; high → eased)
//   t∞: target-frame-budget : 8.33ms @ 120Hz (per W13-1 fps_pipeline contract)
//   t∞: cap-budget-overrun = AdaptiveDegrader engages · per polish_audit
//   t∞: telemetry-emit per-frame · loop-tick + fingerprint + cap-events
//   t∞: MCP-bridge exposes per-frame state for-development-only · cap-gated
//   t∞: synthesis-autonomous · ¬-asks-Apocky-for-permission-per-frame
//   t∞: stage-0 GPU-RGBA-shim transitional · spectral-direct activates when-hw
//
// § REFERENCE
//   compiler-rs/crates/cssl-host-fps-pipeline/         § fps_pipeline triple-buffer
//   compiler-rs/crates/cssl-render-v2/                 § v2 render pipeline
//   compiler-rs/crates/cssl-spectral-render/           § 4-illuminant LUT
//   compiler-rs/crates/cssl-substrate-omega-field/     § ω-field cell store
//   compiler-rs/crates/cssl-host-perf-enforcer/        § frame-budget enforcement
//   compiler-rs/crates/cssl-host-polish-audit/         § AdaptiveDegrader
//   compiler-rs/crates/cssl-analytics-aggregator/      § telemetry-aggregator
//   compiler-rs/crates/cssl-host-mcp-server/           § MCP development bridge
//   Labyrinth of Apocalypse/systems/substrate_intelligence.csl § engine
//   Labyrinth of Apocalypse/systems/crystallization.csl        § ω-field allocator
//   Labyrinth of Apocalypse/systems/alien_materialization.csl  § projector
//   Labyrinth of Apocalypse/systems/intent_translation.csl     § input pipeline
//   Labyrinth of Apocalypse/systems/fps_pipeline.csl           § triple-buffer
//   Labyrinth of Apocalypse/systems/fps_hud.csl                § HUD overlays
//   memory/feedback_engine_is_runtime_procgen   ‼ runtime-compose ¬ static
//   memory/feedback_no_external_llm_for_loa_intelligence ‼ pure-local
//
// § CSSLC-REQUIRES
//   ✓ extern "C" fn-decls (W11+)
//   ✓ const-u32           (W12)
//   ◐ struct-FFI FrameSnapshot ← W17-A in flight
//   ○ f32 fixed-point    ← post-W17 (i32-millis OK at-stage-0)

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// § FRAME-BUDGET · per-mode targets (matches fps_pipeline.csl + W13-1)
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

const FRAME_BUDGET_60HZ_MICROS  : u32 = 16667 ;   // 16.667ms
const FRAME_BUDGET_120HZ_MICROS : u32 = 8333 ;    // 8.333ms · default-target
const FRAME_BUDGET_144HZ_MICROS : u32 = 6944 ;    // 6.944ms · stretch-target
const FRAME_BUDGET_240HZ_MICROS : u32 = 4167 ;    // 4.167ms · esports-tier

fn frame_budget_60hz()  -> u32 { FRAME_BUDGET_60HZ_MICROS }
fn frame_budget_120hz() -> u32 { FRAME_BUDGET_120HZ_MICROS }
fn frame_budget_144hz() -> u32 { FRAME_BUDGET_144HZ_MICROS }
fn frame_budget_240hz() -> u32 { FRAME_BUDGET_240HZ_MICROS }

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// § TEMPORAL-COHERENCE-BUFFER discriminants
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Ring-of-3 substrate-projection-states. The composer blends them per-axis-
// weighted to produce the displayed frame. Different axes drive different
// blend-weights so e.g. high-Solemnity scenes have heavy easing while
// low-Solemnity scenes are snappy.

const TCB_RING_DEPTH        : u32 = 3 ;
const TCB_BLEND_LINEAR      : u32 = 0 ;
const TCB_BLEND_EASE_OUT    : u32 = 1 ;
const TCB_BLEND_EASE_IN_OUT : u32 = 2 ;
const TCB_BLEND_SPRING      : u32 = 3 ;
const TCB_BLEND_INSTANT     : u32 = 4 ;  // no blending · for snappy combat
const TCB_BLEND_COUNT       : u32 = 5 ;

fn tcb_ring_depth()        -> u32 { TCB_RING_DEPTH }
fn tcb_blend_linear()      -> u32 { TCB_BLEND_LINEAR }
fn tcb_blend_ease_out()    -> u32 { TCB_BLEND_EASE_OUT }
fn tcb_blend_ease_in_out() -> u32 { TCB_BLEND_EASE_IN_OUT }
fn tcb_blend_spring()      -> u32 { TCB_BLEND_SPRING }
fn tcb_blend_instant()     -> u32 { TCB_BLEND_INSTANT }

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// § FRAME-LIFECYCLE
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

extern "C" fn di_render_frame_begin(
    observer_coord_cell: u32,
    target_budget_micros: u32,
    cap_token: u32
) -> u32 ;
// Returns FrameContext-handle (ω-field-cell-id). 0 ⇒ Σ-mask-denial.
//
// Allocates :
//   - per-frame ω-field cells for accumulator state
//   - links to the temporal-coherence-buffer ring
//   - kicks-off frame-budget timer (perf-enforcer)
//   - emits telemetry "frame-N-begin"

extern "C" fn di_render_visible_crystals(frame: u32) -> u32 ;
// Queries substrate-knowledge LRU + observer-frustum-cull to produce a
// Crystal-list. Returns array-handle (crystal-id list).

extern "C" fn di_render_crystal_into_frame(frame: u32, crystal: u32) -> u32 ;
// Performs the per-crystal aspect-query → spectral-project → channel-emit
// sequence. Returns 0 = invisible-to-observer (Σ-mask) or aspect-fail ;
// 1 = contributed.

extern "C" fn di_render_temporal_smooth(frame: u32, blend_kind: u32) -> u32 ;
// Pulls last (TCB_RING_DEPTH-1) frames from the ring and blends with
// `blend_kind` weighting. Result is the FINAL projected state for this
// observer's display.

extern "C" fn di_render_emit_channels(
    frame: u32,
    channel_mask: u32,
    output_handles_ptr: u32,
    output_handles_count: u32
) -> u32 ;
// Emits the smoothed projection to each enabled output-channel.
//   bit 0 set : visual-GPU-shim (RGBA framebuffer-handle)
//   bit 1 set : visual-spectral-direct (future-display)
//   bit 2 set : audio-spatial (mixer-handle)
//   bit 3 set : haptic-gamepad
//   bit 4 set : haptic-VR
//   bit 5 set : semantic-overlay
//   bit 6 set : olfactory  (future-hw)
//   bit 7 set : proprioceptive (future-hw)
//   bit 8 set : neural-direct (future-hw)
//   bit 9 set : telemetry-log (always-on)
// Returns count of channels emitted-to.

extern "C" fn di_render_frame_end(frame: u32) -> u32 ;
// Pushes this frame's projection-state into the temporal-coherence-buffer
// ring (oldest is evicted). Records frame-fingerprint into akashic.
// Releases per-frame ω-field cells. Stops budget-timer + emits
// "frame-N-end · used X micros" telemetry.

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// § PERF-ENFORCEMENT · AdaptiveDegrader integration
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Per W13-12 perf-budget-enforcer · if a frame overruns its budget, the
// degrader drops fidelity-tier (e.g., reduce KAN-eval-precision per
// aspect, or skip-blend on temporal-coherence). This is per-cap-gated
// (player can choose : "always max fidelity even if framerate drops"
// or "always smooth framerate · auto-degrade").

extern "C" fn di_render_perf_check(frame: u32, used_micros: u32) -> u32 ;
// Returns verdict :
//   0 = Pass (under budget · keep tier)
//   1 = Over (slight overrun · soften next-frame)
//   2 = Severe (major overrun · drop fidelity tier)
// AdaptiveDegrader reacts based on returned verdict.

extern "C" fn di_render_fidelity_tier(frame: u32) -> u32 ;
// Returns current fidelity tier (0 = max · 7 = min · 8 levels).

extern "C" fn di_render_set_fidelity_tier(tier: u32, cap_token: u32) -> u32 ;
// Player-direct-set (sovereign-override). Σ-mask-gated.

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// § TELEMETRY · per-frame state for-development + replay-determinism
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Apocky-directive-2 : "Utilize the MCP tools and logging and telemetry
// and synthesize it autonomously." This module emits frame-by-frame
// telemetry into cssl-analytics-aggregator + logs into cssl-host-mcp-server
// (the development-only MCP bridge). Both are Σ-mask-cap-gated. Player
// can disable all telemetry via revoke-cap.

extern "C" fn di_telemetry_frame_record(
    frame: u32,
    fingerprint: u32,
    used_micros: u32,
    fidelity_tier: u32
) -> u32 ;
// Pushes a TelemetryRecord into the analytics-aggregator. Returns 0 on
// success. Cap-gated. Aggregator does local-only stats + opt-in
// federated-mycelium-share (per feedback_mycelium_network).

extern "C" fn di_mcp_log_frame(
    frame: u32,
    fingerprint: u32,
    cap_token: u32
) -> u32 ;
// Sends a JSON-RPC notification on the MCP-server channel for-development
// inspection. Σ-mask-gated. Disabled in shipped-builds by default.

extern "C" fn di_mcp_query_active_clients() -> u32 ;
// Returns count of MCP-clients currently subscribed to frame-events.
// 0 in shipped-builds. >0 only when developer-tooling attached.

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// § SYNTHESIS-AUTONOMOUS · self-driving render-loop
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Apocky-directive : "synthesize it autonomously". The render-loop runs
// in its own substrate-tick cadence ; it does not need per-frame Apocky-
// approval (that violates real-time UX). The loop uses :
//   · current ω-field-state (auto-evolving per substrate-tick)
//   · current intent-resolutions from intent_translation
//   · current KAN-bias-state (auto-evolving from observations)
//   · current Σ-mask state (consent-gated · player-revocable any-time)
// to autonomously produce frames. Each frame is attested + telemetered.

extern "C" fn di_render_autonomous_tick(observer_coord_cell: u32, cap_token: u32) -> u32 ;
// Runs one full frame-lifecycle (begin → visible → crystals → smooth →
// emit → end) with default settings. Used by the LoA main-loop. Returns
// FrameContext-handle for the just-completed frame (or 0 on error).

extern "C" fn di_render_autonomous_loop(
    observer_coord_cell: u32,
    target_hz: u32,
    duration_ms: u32,
    cap_token: u32
) -> u32 ;
// Runs the autonomous tick at-target-Hz for-duration-ms. For benchmarking +
// dev-attachment via MCP. Returns count of frames rendered. Σ-mask-gated.

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// § DETERMINISM CONTRACT
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// Replay-determinism over the full render-loop is required :
//   - Same (ω-field-state · observer · target-budget · KAN-state · t)
//     ⇒ same frame-fingerprint
//   - The temporal-coherence-buffer ring is part of the deterministic state
//   - AdaptiveDegrader decisions are deterministic given perf-history-snapshot
//   - Telemetry-records replay-equal across hosts/sessions

extern "C" fn di_replay_compare_frame(
    canonical_fingerprint: u32,
    rerun_fingerprint: u32
) -> u32 ;
// Returns 1 if identical · 0 mismatch (drives fail-fast on replay-divergence).

// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
// § STAGE-0 BOOTSTRAP-SHIM
// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
//
// Until csslc compiles this directly, a Rust shim at
// `compiler-rs/crates/cssl-host-digital-intelligence-render/` mirrors this
// surface and DELEGATES to existing primitives :
//   cssl-host-fps-pipeline      · triple-buffered ring
//   cssl-render-v2              · render-pass orchestrator
//   cssl-spectral-render        · 4-illuminant LUT
//   cssl-substrate-omega-field  · ω-field cell store
//   cssl-host-perf-enforcer     · budget enforcement + AdaptiveDegrader
//   cssl-host-polish-audit      · perf-budget tracker
//   cssl-analytics-aggregator   · telemetry-aggregator
//   cssl-host-mcp-server        · MCP-protocol bridge
//   cssl-host-substrate-intelligence (stage-0-shim · committed THIS-wave)
//
// Per Apocky's stage-0-fallback axiom, the GPU-RGBA channel always works
// today ; future-channels (spectral-direct · neural-direct) activate when
// supporting hardware is detected at-runtime.

